# i18n & RTL

## Single source of truth
`packages/i18n/locales/en.json` and `ar.json` — both apps import via `@venue-pos/i18n`

## Rules
- No hardcoded user-facing strings in JSX
- Add key to **both** locale files before using `t('key')`
- Run `npm run lint:i18n` to verify key parity

## Setup per app
```javascript
import { resources, getDirection } from '@venue-pos/i18n';
// init react-i18next with resources
document.documentElement.dir = getDirection(i18n.language);
```

## RTL Tailwind
Use logical properties: `ms-4`, `me-4`, `ps-4`, `text-start` — not `ml-4`, `text-left`

## DB content (bilingual)
API returns both `nameEn` and `nameAr`; UI picks by active locale:
```javascript
const name = i18n.language === 'ar' ? item.nameAr : item.nameEn;
```

## Kitchen printer
Uses venue default language — not cashier preference (per PRD).
